    name: [StringData(code: "en", text: "Home Maintenance Tasks You Should Do More Often")],
    desc: [StringData(code: "en", text: "Maintaining a house is a big responsibility, but also very rewarding. There are many different areas in your home to maintain, and some need to be serviced more often than others. Doing smaller tasks more often can help reduce your electricity bill, ensure larger costs aren’t accumulated over time, and keep your home cozy and safe for years to come. ")],
    text: [StringData(code: "en", text: "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">Maintaining a house is a big responsibility, but also very rewarding. There are many different areas in your home to maintain, and some need to be serviced more often than others. Doing smaller tasks more often can help reduce your electricity bill, ensure larger costs aren’t accumulated over time, and keep your home cozy and safe for years to come.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Refrigerator Coils</span></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">Your refrigerator can take up to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.artofmanliness.com/articles/keep-your-house-in-tip-top-shape-an-incredibly-handy-home-maintenance-checklist/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(240, 84, 35); transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out 0s; text-decoration: none;\">15 percent</a>&nbsp;of your home’s total electric use. That number can increase if your coils aren’t kept clean to maximize efficiency. You may be asking how to clean the dark and small space underneath or behind this appliance, and the answer is rather simple: vacuum them. Do this once or twice per year.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">HVAC</span><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;Systems and Filters</span></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">Changing your Heating, Ventilation and Air Conditioning (<a href=\"https://www.expertsinyourhome.com/heating-and-air\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(240, 84, 35); transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out 0s; text-decoration: none;\">HVAC</a>) filters is a chore that varies per household. For a smaller home with less air pollutants, think fewer people and no pets, you may be able to change the filters every 2-3 months, but still check them every month. The seasons can also affect maintenance. For example, for months like winter where a family is typically indoors more, the quality of air will be more important.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">The types of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.onegoodthingbyjillee.com/10-important-home-maintenance-tasks/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(240, 84, 35); transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out 0s; text-decoration: none;\">filters</a>&nbsp;also vary. Less expensive filters will last a shorter time than more expensive ones. There are also reusable air filters that will need to be cleaned. Further extend the life of your filters of any kind by cleaning the vents and ducts of your home annually.&nbsp;</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">&nbsp;</h2><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Gutters</span></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">Gutters should always be cleaned twice a year. The best times to clean them are late fall, after all the leaves have fallen, and as part of your spring cleaning. However, at least 4 times a year, the gutters should at least be visually inspected. You can do this by walking around the house to see if there is any sagging and if there are any leaks or holes. For good measure, take a ladder and check your roof and gutters to make sure they are also free of debris or damage after each season.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">If you have more trees around your home, it would be good to check on the gutters more often to ensure they aren’t getting filled with debris. For homeowners in colder areas, also be on the look-out for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.hsh.com/homeowner/home-maintenance-checklist.html\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(240, 84, 35); transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out 0s; text-decoration: none;\">ice dams</a>&nbsp;which can build up and cause water to get into your roof.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Stove Hood/Vent</span></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">This kitchen appliance should be cleaned once a month and even more so depending on use. Think about it, the appliance soaks up smoky, steamy, and greasy air particles to keep your kitchen air clean while you cook and it is bound to get messy.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">To clean the hood, use soapy hot water to wash and then spray down or rinse with sink water. If you need something stronger, use a degreaser, like you would use working around cars, and mix it with a little hot water. Let the hood/vent soak and then rinse it off. Air dry the vent. To help maintain cleanliness and ease monthly cleanings, wash down the vent like you would a counter top or stove top after cooking with a soapy sponge or washcloth.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">These are only a few things that should be done to keep your home well maintained! If you ever need advice or help with home maintenance, we'd be happy to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.expertsinyourhome.com/cleaning/housecleaning\" rel=\" noopener\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(240, 84, 35); transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out 0s; text-decoration: none;\">help</a>&nbsp;with the little and big stuff.&nbsp;</p>")],
    time: DateTime.now(),
    localFile: "blog/2866e1a9-36cd-4261-abeb-1250a4dc93d6.jpg",
    serverPath: "https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/brevix.appspot.com/o/blog%2F2866e1a9-36cd-4261-abeb-1250a4dc93d6.jpg?alt=media&token=56f3d5f4-3f61-4432-8da8-d8516b31fc47",
  ),

  // v1
  BlogData(
    id: "Tau01xOKUrI1b7febATF",
    name: [StringData(code: "en", text: "Trendy Home Technology You Should Try")],
    desc: [StringData(code: "en", text: "Make the most of the time you spend in your home by using the latest trendy home technology that is available. You will probably be amazed at how much more enjoyment you will experience at home when you use technology. Smart technology expands beyond security and thermostats. Now, you can equip your home with robot vacuums, wireless LED bulbs, smart faucets, and even self-sterilizing door handles.")],
    text: [StringData(code: "en", text: "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">Make the most of the time you spend in your home by using the latest trendy home technology that is available. You will probably be amazed at how much more enjoyment you will experience at home when you use technology. Smart technology expands beyond security and thermostats. Now, you can equip your home with robot vacuums, wireless LED bulbs, smart faucets, and even self-sterilizing door handles.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">Technology keeps advancing, and having the ability to tap into these innovations at home is moving beyond luxury and becoming a necessity. A few reasons why you would want to add trendy home technology include:</p><ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px 0px; list-style-position: outside; list-style-image: none; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; margin: 6px 0px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; line-height: 1.5;\">Efficiency – Conserve water, electricity, and save on utility bills by using technology in your home. You are able to control numerous functions with the ease of the touch of a button or use of an app on a phone.</p></li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; margin: 6px 0px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; line-height: 1.5;\">Convenience – Without having to go back home to turn off a light or without even getting out of bed to start the household chores or control the temperature, home technology is easy once it is installed.</p></li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; margin: 6px 0px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; line-height: 1.5;\">Peace of Mind – You can stop worrying about whether or not something was done at your home before you left, and sleep soundly knowing everything is how you want it to be.</p></li><li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; margin: 6px 0px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; line-height: 1.5;\">Customization – Customize everything the way you want them. Set times when a thermostat will make the home warmer or cooler, turn on or off the lights at a specific time of your liking, or set up anything to be done virtually how you want and when you want it done.</p></li></ul><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">Let’s take a look at some of the most convenient innovations and how the latest technology can make your life easier at home. Here are a few of the top trendy technology gadgets to get started.</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Smart Thermostat</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">Perhaps when you think about technology in your home, implementing a temperature gauge that can be controlled remotely may be the first thing that comes to mind. But, how exactly does this work? A smart thermostat is connected through Wi-Fi, allowing you to control the temperature of your home remotely from a smartphone app. Program the temperature settings based on daily schedules, weather conditions, or heating and cooling needs.</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Wireless LED Bulbs</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"https://blog.expertsinyourhome.com/popular-interior-lighting-trends-of-2020\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(240, 84, 35); transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out 0s; text-decoration: none;\">Lighting at home</a>&nbsp;is about more than screwing in a light bulb. You can make it more convenient and intelligent with wireless LED bulbs. LED bulbs use as much as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.energy.gov/energysaver/save-electricity-and-fuel/lighting-choices-save-you-money/led-lighting\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(240, 84, 35); transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out 0s; text-decoration: none;\">75 percent less energy</a>&nbsp;than incandescent lighting. No more need to question whether or not you flicked that light switch off on your way out. Control everything from an app on a smartphone. Schedule lights to turn on or off when you are away, dim them at bedtime, and ultimately save energy with LED technology.</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Robot Vacuums</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">If a small circular remote-controlled vacuum that only holds about a crumb's&nbsp;worth before needing to be emptied is the image that comes to mind when you hear the words, “robot vacuum” then it’s time to take a look at the latest in robot vacuums. They have come a long way and expand beyond carpeting now. Some are even able to wet mop a floor or climb stairs while vacuuming, and you don’t even have to be home to program or control it.</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Smart Faucet</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">You probably waste more water than you’re willing to admit, and all of that water is not only draining the environment but also adding to utility bill costs. When&nbsp;<a href=\"https://blog.expertsinyourhome.com/should-you-install-a-kitchen-faucet-yourself\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(240, 84, 35); transition: all 0.4s ease-in-out 0s; text-decoration: none;\">installed properly</a>, smart faucets help you save up to thousands of gallons per unit per year. Smart faucets are also more hygienic since there is no need to touch the faucet when in use. Control the faucet with your voice or motion sensors. This makes it perfect for families with small children, the elderly, or those living with a disability.</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Self-Sanitizing Door Handles</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">One of the most touched surfaces in your home is the door handle you use to enter and exit every day. You are not the only one touching it. Everyone who reaches to open the door has the potential of spreading germs. The self-sanitizing door handle technology uses UV light to kill germs. This is especially important if you or a loved one you live with is elderly or has a compromised immune system, but it is also great to use with children.</p><h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 10px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(57, 57, 57); font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.1; text-rendering: optimizelegibility;\">Setting Up Technology In Your Home</h2><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 16px 0px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Lato, arial, sans-serif;\">These are just a few of the latest trendy home technology that is currently available. Start saving money on utility bills, and make your home more convenient and accessible to turn your house into a home that is customized the way you want it. The most important step is getting it set up. Once installed, you will be able to start enjoying your home more and saving money. You might even help the environment.</p>")],
    time: DateTime.now(),
    localFile: "blog/0264d19f-3bd1-4bda-bfa0-85967171b40b.jpg",
    serverPath: "https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/brevix.appspot.com/o/blog%2F0264d19f-3bd1-4bda-bfa0-85967171b40b.jpg?alt=media&token=89587daa-b1d8-48e7-b7ab-71dc2fd67969",
  ),

